	[DEPRECATION WARNING] Nested I18n namespace lookup under "activerecord.attributes.order" is no longer supported
<p>Every time we load the rails environment:</p>
<pre>[DEPRECATION WARNING] Nested I18n namespace lookup under "activerecord.attributes.order" is no longer supported</pre>

<h3>We don't care</h3>
<p>We don't.  It's one line, displayed when we start a console or some other rails task.  It doesn't slow anything down.  No harm done.</p>
<h3>Fixed it</h3>
<p>I randomly got annoyed and fixed it.  What is it?  In your i18n yml files, having models nested under each other is deprecated.</p>

<p style="padding-left:30px;"><em>config/locales/en.yml</em></p>
<pre>
en:
  activerecord:
    attributes:
      order:
        line_item:
          column_name: 'Column Name Translation'
</pre>
<br /><br />
See how the LineItem model (line_item:) is under the Order model (order:)?<br />
<br />
Take it out:
<p style="padding-left:30px;"><em>config/locales/en.yml <b>(updated)</b></em></p>
<pre>
en:
  activerecord:
    attributes:
      order:
        order_column_name: 'Some Order Column Translation'
      line_item:
        column_name: 'Column Name Translation'
</pre>

<h1>All better!</h1>
